summary: General fire information for Sand Fire
Evacuations:
Re-population occurring where possible. Area is still under an advisory evacuation. Fire personnel are still active in the area.
 Evacuation center has been suspended due to a continued zero occupancy level. It can re-open if necessary.

Information boards: Beginning Monday, June 10, 3 locations; Station 23(3794 CA-16, Guinda), Boy Scout Camp (16980 Yolo Ave.) and Guinda Corner Store (7530 CA-16).
Road Closures: Hwy 16 closed between Rumsey and Hwy 20.
Cooperating Agencies: CAL FIRE, Cal OES, Yolo County Sheriff, CHP, NBIMT and multiple local government  fire agencies.
Conditions: Weather in the area is expected to be hot.
